BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:43CFG2wCUSKNha_qcQX5f
SUMMARY:DJ 101: Intro to Digital Dejaying
DTSTAMP:20260326T022745Z
DTSTART:20260530T200000Z
DESCRIPTION:Interested in learning more about DJ-ing? In this 3-hour crash 
	course\, students will learn the ins-and-outs of Serato\, playing and mixi
	ng tracks\, finessing your tracks\, and general tips and tricks for digita
	l Dejaying!\n\n*Use of a laptop is required to take part in this class — V
	era has a limited number of laptops available to borrow for membership. If
	 you need one to participate\, please email yewon.k@theveraproject.org to 
	confirm our availability.\n\nhttps://link.dice.fm/U5e17f1c6e22\n\nFrom The
	 Vera Project
URL:https://link.dice.fm/U5e17f1c6e22
LOCATION:305 Harrison Street\, Seattle\, Washington 98109\, United States
X-CALRIPPER-SOURCE:vera-project
CATEGORIES:The Vera Project
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
DURATION:PT3H
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:3WyKpj0XQHCCmQGUBkUvv
SUMMARY:RS 101: Intro to Vera's Recording Studio
DTSTAMP:20260326T022745Z
DTSTART:20260530T200000Z
DESCRIPTION:Get into VERA’s Recording Studio through this 2-hour workshop a
	nd studio orientation! Learn the studio infrastructure including\, bootup\
	, signalflow\, patchbay setup\, mixing desk operation\, and basic Digital 
	Audio Workstation (DAW) integration. During this session\, participants wi
	ll experiment with different ways of running signals from the live room to
	 the computer. Some familiarity with Digital Audio Workstations (i.e. ProT
	ools\, Logic\, Reaper\, Ableton\, etc.) is encouraged.\n\nAfter taking thi
	s course\, students who are new to studio recording should be ready for th
	e multi-week Recording Studio Workshop Series\, as well as having a better
	 grounding for independent research. Students who are experienced with stu
	dio recording may be credentialed for volunteering at studio sessions.\n\n
	https://link.dice.fm/d6c0de28e88b\n\nFrom The Vera Project
URL:https://link.dice.fm/d6c0de28e88b
LOCATION:305 Harrison Street\, Seattle\, Washington 98109\, United States
X-CALRIPPER-SOURCE:vera-project
CATEGORIES:The Vera Project
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
DURATION:PT2H
END:VEVENT
